# Git Most Used Commands Cheat Sheet

## Repository Setup

git init
Initialize a new Git repository in the current folder.

git clone <repo-url>
Download an existing repository from GitHub to your computer.

Example:
git clone https://github.com/user/project.git

---

## Checking Repository State

git status
Shows current branch, changed files, and staged files.

git log
Shows commit history.

git log --oneline --graph
Compact visual history of commits.

---

## Adding and Committing Changes

git add <file>
Stage a specific file.

git add .
Stage all changed files.

git commit -m "message"
Create a commit with a message describing the changes.

---

## Working with Remote Repositories

git remote -v
Show connected remote repositories.

git pull origin main
Fetch and merge latest changes from the remote main branch.

git push origin main
Upload local commits to the remote main branch.

---

## Branch Management

git branch
List all local branches.

git branch dev
Create a new branch named "dev".

git checkout dev
Switch to branch "dev".

git switch dev
Modern command to switch branches.

git checkout -b feature/login
Create and switch to a new branch.

---

## Merging Branches

git checkout main
Switch to main branch.

git merge dev
Merge the dev branch into main.

---

## Undoing Changes

git reset <file>
Unstage a file.

git checkout -- <file>
Discard changes in a file and restore the last committed version.

git reset --hard HEAD
Reset repository to the last commit (dangerous, deletes changes).

---

## Cleaning Repository

git clean -f
Remove untracked files from the working directory.

---

## Typical Development Workflow

1. Pull latest changes
   git pull origin main

2. Create or switch to development branch
   git checkout dev

3. Make code changes

4. Stage files
   git add .

5. Commit changes
   git commit -m "Add new feature"

6. Push changes
   git push origin dev

7. Merge dev into main when ready
   git checkout main
   git merge dev
   git push origin main

---

## Common Branch Strategy

main
Production-ready code.

dev
Development branch.

feature branches
Used for building new features.

Example:
feature/login
feature/payment
feature/dashboard
